8 An Act relating to professions and occupations;
amending 59 O.S. 2021, Section 396.5b, which relates
9 to funeral licensing continuing education courses;
allowing the Oklahoma Funeral Directors Association
10 to approved continuing education credits; and
providing an effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 396.5b, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 396.5b. A. Beginning July 1, 2006, as a condition of
17 renewal or reactivation of a license, each licensee shall submit to
18 the Oklahoma Funeral Board evidence of the completion of clock hours
19 of continuing education courses approved by the Board within the
20 twelve (12) months immediately preceding the term for which the
21 license is issued. The number of hours, or its equivalent, required
22 for each licensed term shall be determined by the Board and
23 promulgated by rule. Each licensee shall be required to complete
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3260 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 and include as part of the continuing education provision a certain
2 number of required subjects as provided by rule.
3 B. The continuing education courses required by this section
4 shall be satisfied by courses approved by the Board, the Oklahoma
5 Funeral Directors Association, or the Academy of Professional
6 Funeral Service Practice.
7 C. The Board shall maintain a listing of courses approved by
8 the Board.
9 D. The Board shall not issue an active renewal license or
10 reactivate a license unless the continuing education requirement set
11 forth in this section is satisfied within the prescribed time
12 period.
13 E. The provisions of this section shall not apply:
14 1. During the period a licensee is on inactive status;
15 2. To a nonresident licensee licensed in this state if the
16 licensee is not engaged in funeral service or embalming practice in
17 Oklahoma; and
18 3. To classes of licensees exempted by rules of the Board.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
20 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON BUSINESS AND INSURANCE
